{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01539izJ1gEevoGFu5gTgbzh","type":"tool_result","content":"Reduce the cluster from 3 nodes to 1 without data loss, and clean up unused PVCs.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Do not install CRDs or use operators.\n- Do not delete PVCs still referenced by running pods.\n\nGOAL:\n- Cluster runs on 1 node with all data available.\n- Only PVCs for active pods remain.\n\nVerification:\n1. Cluster health is yellow/green with 1 node and no unassigned shards.\n2. app-data shards are on the remaining node.\n3. Only PVCs for active ordinals remain.\n4. Remaining pod still has its marker file.===PRECOND===\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n5\n\n[precondition:downscale_seed_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'downscale_seed_fixture':probe] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A --max-time 5 \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_count\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q \"\\\"count\\\"\"'\n\n===AGENT===\n{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"init\",\"cwd\":\"/mydata/karma/runs/short-rerun/elasticsearch-incident-response-chain-20260618_114051/stages/stage_03\",\"session_id\":\"c57fd2be-f1a7-42d7-861a-cca55421b028\",\"tools\":[\"Task\",\"AskUserQuestion\",\"Bash\",\"CronCreate\",\"CronDelete\",\"CronList\",\"DesignSync\",\"Edit\",\"EnterPlanMode\",\"EnterWorktree\",\"ExitPlanMode\",\"ExitWorktree\",\"Monitor\",\"NotebookEdit\",\"PushNotification\",\"Read\",\"RemoteTrigger\",\"ScheduleWakeup\",\"Skill\",\"TaskCreate\",\"TaskGet\",\"TaskList\",\"TaskOutput\",\"TaskStop\",\"TaskUpdate\",\"ToolSearch\",\"WebFetch\",\"WebSearch\",\"Workflow\",\"Write\"],\"mcp_servers\":[],\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-8\",\"permissionMode\":\"bypassPermi